{
  "texts": [
    "Abstract syntaxFigure 1 presents the core concepts of the Impromptu metamodel.",
    "AssetsThe central notion being described is the asset, which can be either prompt, a composer or a prompt chain.",
    "Assets can be annotated with useful information such as description and authors.",
    "The text contents of an asset are written in a particular language, which is identified by its code and region from the ISO standard.",
    "Moreover, assets can be given labels to facilitate organizing and searching catalogs of prompts.In order to keep track of asset versioning, it is possible to provide a version name, date of creation and last update and identify the prior version of the same prompt."
  ]
}